The paper deals with Zero-Shot Learning (ZSL) which is a subfield of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves learning a latent space that captures the common semantic characteristics between the visual modality and the class semantic modality, which is a key aspect of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of attributes or word vectors, which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). Finally, the experimental results involve benchmark datasets of images, which is related to Multimedia (cs.MM).
